HIV/AIDS: Kasashen China sun samu karuwar sabbin masu cutar da kashi 14 cikin 100
China ta ba da rahoton cewa adadin mutanen da ke da cutar HIV da kuma cutar AIDS ya ƙaru da kashi 14 cikin ɗari.
Ma'aikatan kiwon lafiya sun ce mutane fiye da 820,000 ne ke fama da wannan matsalar.
A cikin kwata na biyu na 2018 kadai, an samu sabbin mutane kusan 40,000.
Yawancin sabbin cututtukan sun kasance ta hanyar jima'i, wanda ke nuna canji daga baya.
A al'adance, cutar HIV tana yaduwa cikin sauri a wasu sassan kasar Sin ta hanyar karban jini da ke dauke da cutar.
Amma, adadin mutanen da ke kamuwa da cutar HIV ta wannan hanyar ya ragu sosai, in ji jami'an kiwon lafiya na ƙasar Sin a wani taro a lardin Yunnan.
Amma a shekara guda, adadin mutanen da ke da cutar HIV da cutar AIDS a China ya ƙaru da mutane 100,000.
Yaduwar cutar HIV ta hanyar jima'i babbar matsala ce a cikin al'ummar LGBT na kasar Sin.
An haramta luwadi a kasar Sin a shekarar 1997, amma nuna bambanci ga 'yan LGBTI ya zama ruwan dare gama gari.
Idan aka yi la'akari da dabi'un kasar, bincike ya nuna cewa kashi 70 zuwa 90 cikin dari na maza da ke yin jima'i da maza za su yi aure.
Yawancin cututtukan da ke faruwa a cikin waɗannan ma'aurata suna faruwa ne saboda rashin kariya ta jima'i.
Tun daga shekara ta 2003, gwamnatin kasar Sin ta samar da maganin cutar HIV ga kowa a kasar domin magance cutar.
